  "texts": [
    "When making decisions, the agent retrieves similar driving experiences from analogous scenarios using vector search, thereby aiding in the decision-making process.Safety evaluation criteria: Safety is quantified on a scale from 0 to 10, using Time To Collision (TTC) to measure vehicular safety post-action.",
    "The TTC above 3 seconds indicates optimal safety, earning the highest score of 10.",
    "Below 1.5 seconds, TTC indicates a critical safety risk, scoring 0 [37]- [39].",
    "For TTC values between 1.5 and 3 seconds, the safety score linearly scales from 0 to 10.",
    "Saf etyscore (t) =      20(T T C(t)-1.5) 3, if 1.5s < T T C(t) < 3s 10, else if T T C(t) > 3s 0, otherwise.Efficiency evaluation criteria: Efficiency is similarly rated on a scale from 0 to 10 and uses speed as the efficiency metric."
